                     <div id="comment-27234" class="issue-data-block activity-comment twixi-block expanded">
    <div class="twixi-wrap verbose actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-opened"><span>Hide</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-links">
            <a href="/browse/SHBL-24?focusedCommentId=27234&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-27234" title="A permanent link to this comment." class="icon icon-perma"><span>Permalink</span></a>
                                </div>
        <div class="action-details">
    
    
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="aalto" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27234_verbose" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aalto">Erkki Aalto</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27234_verbose subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='21/Aug/09 4:15 AM'><time datetime='2009-08-21T04:15-0700'>21/Aug/09 4:15 AM</time></span></span>  </div>
        <div class="action-body flooded"><p>Juhani seems to be on holiday, but I hope he'll contact soon. I realized a very important reason why local accounts should be supported (should have thought this from the beginning): If only shibboleth authentication is possible, it is not possible to use the confluence API in scripts, at  least not to do anything useful. I personally would like to get rid of self created local accounts, but we'll always need privileged local accounts for administrative scripts. Using shibboleth authetication only will never be possible. </p> </div>
    </div>
    <div class="twixi-wrap concise actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-closed"><span>Show</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-details flooded">
            
    
    
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="aalto" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27234_concise" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aalto">Erkki Aalto</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27234_concise subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='21/Aug/09 4:15 AM'><time datetime='2009-08-21T04:15-0700'>21/Aug/09 4:15 AM</time></span></span>               Juhani seems to be on holiday, but I hope he'll contact soon. I realized a very important reason why local accounts should be supported (should have thought this from the beginning): If only shibboleth authentication is possible, it is not possible to use the confluence API in scripts, at  least not to do anything useful. I personally would like to get rid of self created local accounts, but we'll always need privileged local accounts for administrative scripts. Using shibboleth authetication only will never be possible.          </div>
