                     <div id="comment-27314" class="issue-data-block activity-comment twixi-block expanded">
    <div class="twixi-wrap verbose actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-opened"><span>Hide</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-links">
            <a href="/browse/SHBL-24?focusedCommentId=27314&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-27314" title="A permanent link to this comment." class="icon icon-perma"><span>Permalink</span></a>
                                </div>
        <div class="action-details">
    
    
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="hans-ulrich.pieper@fu-berlin.de" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27314_verbose" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hans-ulrich.pieper%40fu-berlin.de">Hans-Ulrich Pieper</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27314_verbose subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='25/Aug/09 8:03 AM'><time datetime='2009-08-25T08:03-0700'>25/Aug/09 8:03 AM</time></span></span>  </div>
        <div class="action-body flooded"><p>Dear Erkki, dear Gary,</p>

<p>we experienced the same problem as Erkki since version 1.5./1.6 and i agree, that it would be nice to have a 	sustainable solution. We need authentication with both, shibboleth and local accounts too. We want to offer access to wikis for students, faculty at the "Freie Universität Berlin" (authenticated by our IdP) and external users, whose accounts cannot be authenticated by any Identy Provider. We have implemented a loginpage, where users can choose between "Local Accounts" and "Shibboleth Accounts". </p>

<p>What we found out:<br/>
In version 1.4 the LoginFilter com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter (see confluence/WE-INF/web.xml) <br/>
and the methode public Principal getUser(HttpServletRequest <br/>
request, HttpServletResponse response) in RemoteUserAuthenticatior.java was used.</p>

<p>From version 1.5 the LoginFilter is now based on shibauth.confluence.authentication.shibboleth.ShibLoginFilter using the method public boolean login(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response, String <br/>
username, String password, boolean cookie).</p>

<p>A Colleague implemented a workarround using the old LoginFilter com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter and modifying the class  RemoteUserAuthenticator. I don't think, it is the smartest solution, but it works. If requested, we can provide the modified remoteUserAuth-1.6.jar.</p>

<p>Kind regards Hans-Ulrich</p> </div>
    </div>
    <div class="twixi-wrap concise actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-closed"><span>Show</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-details flooded">
            
    
    
    
                

