                     <div id="comment-27318" class="issue-data-block activity-comment twixi-block expanded">
    <div class="twixi-wrap verbose actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-opened"><span>Hide</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-links">
            <a href="/browse/SHBL-24?focusedCommentId=27318&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-27318" title="A permanent link to this comment." class="icon icon-perma"><span>Permalink</span></a>
                                </div>
        <div class="action-details">
    
    
                                            
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="gswduke" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27318_verbose" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gswduke">Gary S. Weaver</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27318_verbose subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='25/Aug/09 8:54 AM'><time datetime='2009-08-25T08:54-0700'>25/Aug/09 8:54 AM</time></span></span>   - <span class="redText subText" title="Gary S. Weaver - 25/Aug/09 8:56 AM">edited</span> </div>
        <div class="action-body flooded"><p>Ok, here's what I've found so far:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Between 1.4 and 1.5, Bruc Liong added ShibLoginFilter and we added info in the release notes about needing to edit web.xml to use the new login filter.</li>
	<li>It appears though (I might be wrong, but you could check) that you <b>might</b> be able to use the old LoginFilter (com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter) in your web.xml, but I'm not sure. This would mean that in web.xml you would have:
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
<p>and not</p>
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;shibauth.confluence.authentication.shibboleth.ShibLoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
<p>as it indicated in release notes.</p></li>
	<li>The following configuration property was added in the shib auth plugin 1.5, so if you are not using ShibLoginFilter, then you would need to be sure you have this set in your <em>remoteUserAuthenticator.properties</em>:
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">update.last.login.date=<span class="code-keyword">true</span></pre>
</div></div></li>
</ul>


<p>Hans-Ulrich, could you provide the updated source code (and pom.xml, etc.) for the changes that your colleague made? If so, Bruc and/or I can look at them we will be happy to see whether we can merge those changes (perhaps making them optional?) into the shibboleth authenticator plugin.</p>

<p>I apologize to you and Erkki that these changes caused you trouble. Unfortunately, I still don't understand how the old LoginFilter allowed you to login either via Shibboleth or with Confluence accounts, so if you could explain that also (how you have it configured, how exactly people could login via Shib or Confluence, because it seems that Shib would reject someone who didn't pass Shib authentication), I could add that to our documentation (unless you would like to- you are welcome to) so that we might be able to help others with a similar issue. I would like to just be able to patch the plugin, but unfortunately I don't see any code changes that need to be made, and I don't have an environment setup to be able to test it, so I will look forward to your response.</p>

<p>Thanks so much!<br/>
Gary</p> </div>
    </div>
    <div class="twixi-wrap concise actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-closed"><span>Show</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-details flooded">
            
    
    
                                            
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="gswduke" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27318_concise" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gswduke">Gary S. Weaver</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27318_concise subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='25/Aug/09 8:54 AM'><time datetime='2009-08-25T08:54-0700'>25/Aug/09 8:54 AM</time></span></span>   - <span class="redText subText" title="Gary S. Weaver - 25/Aug/09 8:56 AM">edited</span>              Ok, here's what I've found so far:
<ul>
	<li>Between 1.4 and 1.5, Bruc Liong added ShibLoginFilter and we added info in the release notes about needing to edit web.xml to use the new login filter.</li>
	<li>It appears though (I might be wrong, but you could check) that you <b>might</b> be able to use the old LoginFilter (com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter) in your web.xml, but I'm not sure. This would mean that in web.xml you would have:
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
and not
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;shibauth.confluence.authentication.shibboleth.ShibLoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
as it indicated in release notes.</li>
	<li>The following configuration property was added in the shib auth plugin 1.5, so if you are not using ShibLoginFilter, then you would need to be sure you have this set in your <em>remoteUserAuthenticator.properties</em>:
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">update.last.login.date=<span class="code-keyword">true</span></pre>
</div></div></li>
</ul>


Hans-Ulrich, could you provide the updated source code (and pom.xml, etc.) for the changes that your colleague made? If so, Bruc and/or I can look at them we will be happy to see whether we can merge those changes (perhaps making them optional?) into the shibboleth authenticator plugin.

I apologize to you and Erkki that these changes caused you trouble. Unfortunately, I still don't understand how the old LoginFilter allowed you to login either via Shibboleth or with Confluence accounts, so if you could explain that also (how you have it configured, how exactly people could login via Shib or Confluence, because it seems that Shib would reject someone who didn't pass Shib authentication), I could add that to our documentation (unless you would like to- you are welcome to) so that we might be able to help others with a similar issue. I would like to just be able to patch the plugin, but unfortunately I don't see any code changes that need to be made, and I don't have an environment setup to be able to test it, so I will look forward to your response.

Thanks so much!
Gary         </div>
    </div>
</div>
