                     <div id="comment-27336" class="issue-data-block activity-comment twixi-block expanded">
    <div class="twixi-wrap verbose actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-opened"><span>Hide</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-links">
            <a href="/browse/SHBL-24?focusedCommentId=27336&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-27336" title="A permanent link to this comment." class="icon icon-perma"><span>Permalink</span></a>
                                </div>
        <div class="action-details">
    
    
    
                

    <a class="user-hover user-avatar" rel="gswduke" style="background-image:url(/secure/useravatar?size=small&amp;avatarId=10182);"  id="commentauthor_27336_verbose" href="/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gswduke">Gary S. Weaver</a>
 added a comment  - <span class='commentdate_27336_verbose subText'><span class='date user-tz' title='25/Aug/09 12:18 PM'><time datetime='2009-08-25T12:18-0700'>25/Aug/09 12:18 PM</time></span></span>  </div>
        <div class="action-body flooded"><p>attaching remoteUserAuth-1.7-SNAPSHOT.jar and remoteUserAuthenticator.properties</p>

<p>I made the changes submitted by Freie Universität Berlin the default behavior, which will require manual change to web.xml to use whatever other login filter you want to use such as:</p>
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;com.atlassian.seraph.filter.LoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
<p>If someone wishes to use </p>
<div class="code panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="codeContent panelContent">
<pre class="code-java">&lt;filter-name&gt;login&lt;/filter-name&gt;
&lt;filter-class&gt;shibauth.confluence.authentication.shibboleth.ShibLoginFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;</pre>
</div></div>
<p>then from 1.7 on, it will require web.xml to be modified to use ShibLoginFilter per above and will require using.shib.login.filter=true to be uncommented in the properties, but then they would possibly encounter the issue noted in this ticket. But for Helsinki and Freie Universität Berlin, you would not want to set that to true and you'd want to modify web.xml to NOT use ShibLoginFilter.</p>

<p>Also in this jar/config is new functionality to allow the ability to get full name using regex from the header value supplied by Shibboleth SP. See the attached config file remoteUserAuthenticator.properties for an example of how you could do this. Please watch <a href="/browse/SHBL-28" title="Add ability to create fullname using replace and regex similar to remoteuser mapping"><del>SHBL-28</del></a> and comment on that functionality there if you have time. That way they can use this plugin without modifications. Please let me know what you think. I felt like I was going overboard by using regexp for your specific case, but it is consistent with the way remote user mapping was implemented (copied/pasted Bruc's code) which is the most flexible solution that could possibly help others use the plugin that couldn't before also.</p> </div>
    </div>
    <div class="twixi-wrap concise actionContainer">
        <a href="#" class="twixi"><span class="icon twixi-closed"><span>Show</span></span></a>
        <div class="action-details flooded">
            
    
    
    
                

