I explained the reason why logging in with a local account got broken in the comments of issue <a href="http://studio.plugins.atlassian.com/browse/SHBL-15">http://studio.plugins.atlassian.com/browse/SHBL-15</a>

To summarize:

It (the local account stuff) got broken when you introduced the login filter and overrided the login method in the authenticator. Confluence seems to call the login method of the configured seraph authenticator when someone tries to login with the normal Confluence login form. In the previous versions you hadn't overridden the login method so the one inherited (normal confluence login) was called.

In my point of view overriding the login method is unnecessary and the login filter only makes the setup of the authenticator more difficult. I can't see them improving anything (see comments in <a href="/browse/SHBL-15" title="The authenticator is a resource hog"><del>SHBL-15</del></a>) by Scott Cantor and me.

Anyway I'm again working with Shibboleth / Confluence stuff so I'll be actually active with this. And I haven't had a chance to look at the newest code so excuse me if this is already fixed in some way. <img class="emoticon" src="/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif" height="20" width="20" align="absmiddle" alt="" border="0"/>

